{"word":"H1721 - דֹּדָנִים - Dôdânîym - do-daw-neem' - Dodanim","slug":"H1721","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דֹּדָנִים</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Dôdânîym"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>do-daw-neem'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dodanim"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E8;&#x05D3;&#x05E0;&#x05D9;&#x05DD;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D3;&#x05E0;&#x05D9;&#x05DD; - do&#x0302;da&#x0302;n&#x0131;&#x0302;ym  ro&#x0302;da&#x0302;n&#x0131;&#x0302;ym</b> - <i>do-daw-neem', ro-daw-neem'</i><p/>The second form is used by orthographical error in <a href='B:130 1:7'>1Ch 1:7</a>. A plural of uncertain derivation; <i>Dodanites</i>, or descendants of a son of Javan: - Dodanim."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1719\">H1719</a>, <a href=\"#/H7290\">H7290</a>, <a href=\"#/H8639\">H8639</a>"}]}